[I] Language to translate the mathematical model of a problem into a LP or MIP program

[T] ZIMPL is a little language to translate the mathematical model of a problem
[T] into a linear or (mixed-)integer mathematical program expressed in .lp or
[T] .mps file format which can be read by a LP or MIP solver.

[U] https://github.com/scipopt/zimpl

[A] SCIP Project
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/development
[F] CROSS

